  <li>
    <p>Rambert learned <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="to his chagrin - (chagrin - \ shə-ˈgrin , British usually ˈsha-grin \ 懊恼)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(让他倍感失望的是)</code></b> that Cottard didn’t know where Gonzales lived; he suggested that they’d better pay another visit to the small café. They made an appointment for the following day.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Next morning Cottard and Rambert went off to the cafe and left a message for Garcia, asking him to come that evening, or if this could not be <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="managed"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(可以安排出[时间]来参加)</code></b>, next day.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>“Tomorrow evening,” Gonzales continued, “we’ll look up the kids and try to <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="get a real move on - (get a move on - 抓紧做)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(抓紧时间，真正行动起来)</code></b>.”</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>“Courage. I know now that man is capable of great deeds. But if he isn’t capable of a great emotion, well, he <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="leaves me cold"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(未能打动某人/提不起某人的兴趣)</code></b>.”</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>When Rieux <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="gave him to understand"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(告诉/告知/通知他)</code></b> that he’d like to be <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="kept posted"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(让他了解最新消息)</code></b>, Rambert proposed that he and Tarrou should <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="look him up"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(联系/寻找他)</code></b> one night at the end of the week.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Quite possibly Gonzales and the two youngsters hadn’t been able to get through the cordon. All he could do was to put them in touch once more with Raoul. Naturally this couldn’t be done before <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="the next day but one - (除了明天后的第二天 - 后天)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(后天)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>“A dog or a <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="get-away"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(逃犯)</code></b>,” Tarrou remarked.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>“You know, Doctor, I’ve given a lot of thought to your campaign. And if I’m not with you, I have my reasons. No, I don’t think it’s that I’m afraid to <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="risk my skin"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(冒着生命危险)</code></b> again. I took part in the Spanish Civil War.”</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>On the next day but one, Raoul, whom Rambert met at a street corner, confirmed Garcia’s surmise; the <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="low-lying districts"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(低洼地区)</code></b> had, in fact, been isolated and a cordon put round them.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>“Rather a boring record,” Rambert remarked. “And this must be the tenth time I’ve <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="put it on"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(放[唱片])</code></b> today.”</p>
  </li>
</ol>
